me just stopped short.

01:41.049 --> 01:42.957
Because there's a stop sign.

01:42.959 --> 01:44.377
You should be more alert.

01:44.379 --> 01:45.987
Well maybe if you were
actually teaching me

01:45.989 --> 01:48.712
how to drive and not
putting on your lipstick.

01:50.299 --> 01:52.982
I think you inherited the
bad driving gene from me.

01:53.019 --> 01:54.597
No, I just need more practice.

01:54.599 --> 01:56.712
You promised we'd go twice a week.

01:56.729 --> 01:59.329
Why don't you get a
boyfriend to drive you around.

01:59.346 --> 02:01.546
Right, right, your
solution to everything.

02:01.753 --> 02:04.630
Well when I was your age, I had several.

02:04.632 --> 02:05.942
What about Evan?

02:06.129 --> 02:07.792
Evan doesn't drive.

02:07.939 --> 02:10.431
Anyway, the person has to be over 25.

02:11.158 --> 02:12.608
Why don't you ask your dad?

02:13.279 --> 02:15.029
You'll mind him, he has a daughter.

02:18.529 --> 02:19.362
God!

02:25.142 --> 02:27.309
Hey, learn how to drive!

02:32.058 --> 02:34.725
Oh, that must be Silvia's son.

02:38.093 --> 02:39.010
Poor thing.

02:48.759 --> 02:50.052
You must be Vince.

02:50.239 --> 02:51.672
Uh, yeah.

02:52.289 --> 02:54.112
So good to finally meet you.

02:54.449 --> 02:56.324
Your mom told me so much about you.

02:56.326 --> 02:57.452
And you are?

02:57.459 --> 02:58.596
- I'm Nancy.
- Oh.

02:58.849 --> 03:01.089
I live next door, and your mom

03:01.609 --> 03:03.162
was a wonderful friend.

03:03.429 --> 03:05.777
Aw, thank you, it's
very nice of you to say.

03:05.779 --> 03:07.429
And this is Sarah, my daughter.

03:07.637 --> 03:08.612
- Hi.
- Hi.

03:09.199 --> 03:10.032
She's shy.

03:10.701 --> 03:11.967
So how long you gonna stay?

03:11.969 --> 03:13.357
Just to get the place ready.

03:13.359 --> 03:14.192
Ready?

03:14.509 --> 03:15.652
We're selling it.

03:17.659 --> 03:18.492
Of course.

03:19.269 --> 03:20.277
Is Elizabeth coming?

03:20.279 --> 03:22.022
No no no, just me for now.

03:23.309 --> 03:26.607
Well, please, if
there's anything you need,

03:26.609 --> 03:28.482
don't hesitate to come by.

03:29.116 --> 03:29.977
Okay, I appreciate that.

03:29.979 --> 03:33.282
Just me and Sarah, don't be a stranger.

03:33.949 --> 03:36.212
All right, it was nice meeting you both.

03:36.340 --> 03:37.173
You too.

03:41.656 --> 03:42.487
What?

03:42.489 --> 03:43.322
He's cute.

03:43.859 --> 03:45.542
He's younger than you.

03:45.840 --> 03:46.673
So?

03:46.829 --> 03:49.512
So, isn't that
like against your rules?

03:50.379 --> 03:51.562
You do have a point.

03:52.549 --> 03:54.749
I don't have time to
waste on a younger man.

03:55.719 --> 03:57.469
Glad you've thought this through.

03:57.699 --> 03:58.692
I'm going in.

04:00.099 --> 04:00.932
Come on.

04:05.483 --> 04:08.809
Curvy, feminine, fun-loving woman

04:09.149 --> 04:11.642
in her mid-40s,

04:12.029 --> 04:13.969
no, in her

04:15.969 --> 04:16.802
prime.

04:17.849 --> 04:19.742
Looking, hey, Sarah!

04:21.209 --> 04:22.041
Sarah!

04:22.259 --> 04:23.090
What?

04:23.092 --> 04:23.923
Will you come here a minute?

04:23.925 --> 04:25.489
I wanna show you something.

04:26.000 --> 04:26.833
For a,

04:28.019 --> 04:30.142
should I, come here, I wanna show you.

04:30.529 --> 04:31.540
Look, come here.

04:31.542 --> 04:33.537
Mom, I really wanna finish this piece.

04:33.539 --> 04:35.127
Oh, you can take a break from your

04:35.129 --> 04:36.827
painting for one second.

04:36.829 --> 04:38.452
Just come here, look.

04:39.509 --> 04:40.340
All right, what do you think that...

04:40.342 --> 04:42.653
Is that, curvy woman in her prime?

04:42.655 --> 04:45.137
All right, look, can you
please take a picture?

04:45.139 --> 04:46.786
Because, I tried to take...

04:47.379 --> 04:48.807
Can you just take a selfie?

04:48.809 --> 04:51.452
I did, look at this, it's terrible.

04:51.829 --> 04:53.602
Yeah, you have to hold it higher.

04:56.139 --> 04:57.602
Up, higher.

04:58.869 --> 04:59.700
Yeah.

04:59.702 --> 05:00.709
Is that how they do that?

05:00.989 --> 05:01.822
See?

05:02.519 --> 05:04.269
Good, okay, have fun.

06:20.122 --> 06:22.705
Hi, Vince, it's Mom.

06:23.879 --> 06:25.762
I just spoke with Margot.

06:26.239 --> 06:28.854
Honey, I hope you're doing all right.

06:28.856 --> 06:30.800
Call me back, sweetheart.

06:40.054 --> 06:41.887
Vince, it's Mom again.

06:42.189 --> 06:44.222
Why aren't you returning my calls?

06:45.059 --> 06:47.037
I hope you're taking care of yourself.

06:47.039 --> 06:48.482
I know how you can get.

06:50.009 --> 06:50.842
Call me.

06:52.170 --> 06:53.003
Love you.

07:51.979 --> 07:52.810
Hey.

07:52.812 --> 07:53.799
I'm outside.

07:54.339 --> 07:55.172
I'm busy.

07:55.249 --> 07:57.012
Come on, open up.

07:57.330 --> 07:58.163
Ohhh.

08:06.986 --> 08:07.817
So I wonder if Sarah will go

08:07.819 --> 08:08.887
to the new Transformers tonight.

08:08.889 --> 08:09.889
Forget it.

08:10.469 --> 08:11.469
Come on it'll fun.

08:11.910 --> 08:13.732
No, I wanna keep working on this.

08:13.999 --> 08:14.832
Can I see it?

08:15.589 --> 08:16.422
No.

08:16.949 --> 08:17.842
Come on.

08:18.839 --> 08:19.912
Show it to me.

08:20.659 --> 08:21.492
Just once.

08:23.569 --> 08:24.402
Dream on.

08:35.539 --> 08:36.373
Oh my God.

08:42.389 --> 08:43.552
Are you okay?

08:43.759 --> 08:45.152
I'm fine, thank you.

08:47.349 --> 08:48.542
Let me help you.

08:48.559 --> 08:50.414
Oh no no no no no no, ow, don't do that.

08:50.416 --> 08:51.247
Oh sorry.

08:51.249 --> 08:52.082
It's okay, it's okay.

08:53.259 --> 08:54.092
Gosh.

08:54.788 --> 08:56.347
Oh, I don't know how
I'm gonna get this place

08:56.349 --> 08:57.207
cleaned up in a month.

08:57.209 --> 08:58.042
A month?

08:58.759 --> 09:00.817
Yeah, actually a little less than that.

09:00.819 --> 09:02.852
Oh my God, you need help.

09:03.759 --> 09:05.082
Hold on, Sarah?

09:06.329 --> 09:07.922
Check out this video,
it's just a little fuzzy.

09:09.263 --> 09:10.596
Sarah?

09:11.739 --> 09:12.572
What?

09:13.249 --> 09:15.257
Can you come
down and join us please?

09:15.259 --> 09:16.257
Evan's here.

09:16.259 --> 09:17.852
It's okay, just for a second.

09:19.599 --> 09:20.432
Fine.

09:21.549 --> 09:22.382
Come on.

09:24.689 --> 09:26.189
I have a great idea.

09:28.099 --> 09:28.932
What's up?

09:29.299 --> 09:32.357
Vince just told me that
he's only got a few days,

09:32.359 --> 09:35.312
well a few weeks, to
clean out his mom's house.

09:35.789 --> 09:36.620
Okay.

09:36.622 --> 09:38.572
And you need driving lessons.

09:38.889 --> 09:41.621
Oh, I doubt that she
wants to spend her summer

09:41.623 --> 09:43.066
cleaning up my mom's, I
don't think that's a...

09:43.068 --> 09:44.257
If she wants to get
her license, she does.

09:44.259 --> 09:45.527
I've been very busy.

09:45.529 --> 09:47.977
Maybe if you didn't
go on all those dates.

09:47.979 --> 09:48.997
Honey, please.

09:48.999 --> 09:50.284
Thank you, but I'll
figure it out, I will.

09:50.286 --> 09:52.572
You really need help, don't you?

09:52.759 --> 09:55.092
And you really want
driving lessons, right?

09:55.449 --> 09:56.902
So now's your chance.

09:58.949 --> 09:59.782
Perfect.

09:59.949 --> 10:02.197
Okay, I gotta go, so
why don't you help Vince

10:02.199 --> 10:03.722
clean up this mess now?

10:04.438 --> 10:05.271
You stink.

10:08.639 --> 10:09.532
I gotta bounce.

10:11.929 --> 10:14.579
You don't have to do this,
you do know that, right?

10:15.919 --> 10:18.832
It's the only way I'll get
my license before I'm 30.

10:21.049 --> 10:22.527
But if I'm in your way, then I...

10:22.529 --> 10:25.237
No no no no, no, I could
actually use the help,

10:25.239 --> 10:26.189
so that'd be great.

10:27.129 --> 10:27.962
Okay.

10:28.899 --> 10:30.167
How about we get started tomorrow?

10:30.169 --> 10:33.372
That'll give me a day to organize things.

10:34.789 --> 10:35.620
Okay?

10:35.622 --> 10:36.453
Sure.

10:36.455 --> 10:37.288
Cool.

10:39.949 --> 10:40.782
See ya.

11:00.469 --> 11:03.346
I need a sexy, this is not a sexy one.

11:28.097 --> 11:29.251
Hey.

11:29.253 --> 11:30.982
Oh, hey, how are you?

11:32.096 --> 11:35.192
At least you organized all this stuff.

11:36.769 --> 11:39.352
Yeah, I didn't quite
get as far as I had hoped.

11:40.819 --> 11:42.122
So where should I start?

11:43.260 --> 11:44.732
Uh, good question.

11:46.039 --> 11:49.039
Let me show you around, and
then we can figure it out, yeah?

11:49.579 --> 11:50.929
Cool, watch your head here.

11:52.259 --> 11:54.667
So we need to go through all these.

11:54.669 --> 11:56.707
I think most of this side and that there

11:56.709 --> 11:58.232
is probably my mom's stuff.

11:59.599 --> 12:01.647
My sister should be coming
sometime in the next week

12:01.649 --> 12:02.867
or two to get her stuff too.

12:02.869 --> 12:04.862
And yeah, so, I guess that's it.

12:05.509 --> 12:06.902
Sorry, so that's,

12:07.839 --> 12:08.670
tight quarters.

12:08.672 --> 12:10.892
That's the tour, I guess.

12:14.919 --> 12:15.752
Ohh.

12:18.449 --> 12:21.052
So, what do you do in the real world?

12:22.659 --> 12:25.012
I'm getting my PhD in philosophy.

12:25.789 --> 12:26.622
Cool.

12:27.579 --> 12:29.529
How long does something like that take?

12:30.889 --> 12:31.979
In my case, like

12:33.709 --> 12:34.542
eight years.

12:35.719 --> 12:38.372
Is it supposed to take that long?

12:38.518 --> 12:40.018
No, not exactly.

12:40.364 --> 12:41.414
So what's it about?

12:42.369 --> 12:43.202
Ethics.

12:44.269 --> 12:45.422
What about ethics?

12:45.829 --> 12:47.379
Acting on the motive of duty.

12:47.459 --> 12:50.209
Basically, arguing that we
can always do what is right.

12:52.391 --> 12:54.322
But what if you don't know what's right?

12:54.469 --> 12:55.977
Well, once you recognize
what you oughta do,

12:55.979 --> 12:57.379
then you can actually do it.

12:58.359 --> 13:00.597
Okay, but what if I
think is right isn't what

13:00.599 --> 13:02.012
other people think is right?

13:02.389 --> 13:04.262
Who decides what's right anyway?

13:05.469 --> 13:07.662
I guess you'll just
have to read my thesis.

13:08.679 --> 13:10.222
Yeah, I'd like that.

13:11.749 --> 13:13.999
No, you probably
wouldn't actually.

13:15.199 --> 13:16.912
So how do you like Findlay?

13:20.029 --> 13:20.862
Whatever.

13:21.769 --> 13:24.262
The teachers are good,
they pretend to care.

13:24.729 --> 13:27.222
I don't know, I'm just
ready for whatever's next.

13:28.487 --> 13:30.367
When I was there, all anyone cared about

13:30.369 --> 13:32.097
was football, or theater.

13:32.099 --> 13:32.979
Or theater?

13:34.639 --> 13:36.022
Then nothing's changed.

13:38.399 --> 13:39.299
So what is next?

13:39.569 --> 13:43.337
Oh, um, I guess I'll
start on one of these boxes.

13:43.339 --> 13:46.362
No no no, you said you're
ready for whatever's next.

13:48.029 --> 13:50.002
I'd like to travel.

13:52.769 --> 13:54.572
Go to Europe, see some art.

13:54.729 --> 13:56.987
Europe's great, I
spent some time in Spain

13:56.989 --> 13:58.989
after undergrad, actually almost stayed.

13:59.219 --> 14:01.282
I'd like to go to Germany and Austria.

14:01.399 --> 14:02.399
What's in Austria?

14:02.559 --> 14:04.359
My favorite painters are Austrian.

14:05.009 --> 14:07.752
Like Egon Schiele, Kokoscha.

14:09.949 --> 14:11.589
No idea, never heard of them.

14:11.659 --> 14:14.022
They've totally shaped my style.

14:14.089 --> 14:15.989
I guess that sounds pretentious but

14:17.258 --> 14:19.067
there's just this intensity to their work,

14:19.069 --> 14:20.482
like it grabs you.

14:21.089 --> 14:22.767
I want people to feel something

14:22.769 --> 14:24.482
when they look at my paintings.

14:27.069 --> 14:28.732
So what do you think about this guy?

14:29.329 --> 14:32.092
Mm, no comment.

14:32.749 --> 14:36.037
What, this beautiful
explosion of primary colors

14:36.039 --> 14:36.962
doesn't move you?

14:37.269 --> 14:38.102
Come on.

14:38.649 --> 14:39.899
So what, donate?

14:42.259 --> 14:43.422
Is it that bad?

14:43.639 --> 14:44.472
Trash?

14:44.599 --> 14:45.599
It's for the best.

14:47.538 --> 14:49.205
You're killing me.

15:05.591 --> 15:08.180
(Nancy laughing

15:08.252 --> 15:10.002
Shh, don't wake up Sarah.

15:10.554 --> 15:11.574
We wouldn't want that.

15:11.576 --> 15:12.642
Nooo.

15:17.061 --> 15:17.894
Stop it.

16:12.570 --> 16:14.457
Hey hey hey hey, hold on, hold on.

16:14.459 --> 16:16.159
I got it, let me get that for you.

16:18.181 --> 16:19.931
- Thanks.
- Of course.

16:20.198 --> 16:21.031
Ahhh.

16:21.829 --> 16:25.082
This trade-off requires no heavy
lifting for you, all right?

16:25.129 --> 16:25.962
Got it.

16:26.649 --> 16:27.492
Who's hungry?

16:30.919 --> 16:33.402
What happened to your girlfriend, Vince?

16:33.509 --> 16:34.847
I mean, your mother made it sound like

16:34.849 --> 16:36.132
it was pretty serious.

16:36.509 --> 16:37.659
Just didn't work out.

16:38.549 --> 16:40.022
Wanna be more specific?

16:40.349 --> 16:41.599
No, not really.

16:43.809 --> 16:45.167
I'll find someone for you.

16:45.169 --> 16:46.000
I'm good.

16:46.002 --> 16:47.549
I mean, if I were 10 years younger,

16:47.809 --> 16:50.316
I woulda found her already if
you know what I mean.

16:51.059 --> 16:52.859
Everyone knows what you mean, Mom.

16:53.279 --> 16:54.112
Mm-hmm.

16:55.089 --> 16:56.939
There is a girl at work, though, that

16:57.209 --> 16:59.259
I really like, she's nice and pretty and,

16:59.869 --> 17:00.919
I think she's single.

17:01.909 --> 17:04.317
I'm good, I'm kinda taking
a break from relationships

17:04.319 --> 17:06.118
right now, but thanks for the offer.

17:06.169 --> 17:07.662
You're almost 40.

17:08.479 --> 17:11.329
You don't have time to take
a break, don't you want kids?

17:11.809 --> 17:14.012
I don't know, I can't
really answer that question.

17:14.319 --> 17:16.267
It's the greatest
pleasure of life, look,

17:16.269 --> 17:18.112
well not that she's a prime example.

17:18.128 --> 17:21.017
Sarah's actually
been a huge help already.

17:21.019 --> 17:22.219
She's been really great.

17:23.039 --> 17:24.489
That's a nice thing to say.

17:25.009 --> 17:27.311
I am really glad this
is working out so well.

17:27.950 --> 17:28.900
Okay, I have to go.

17:28.999 --> 17:29.972
Be good, you two.

17:29.999 --> 17:31.849
Bye, thank you for the food, Nancy.

17:32.009 --> 17:33.182
You're welcome.

17:33.439 --> 17:34.592
Interesting woman.

17:35.919 --> 17:37.792
She certainly has a lot of energy.

17:38.549 --> 17:40.049
That's a nice way to put it.

17:41.896 --> 17:43.207
So what do you say we drive this stuff

17:43.209 --> 17:44.259
to Goodwill tomorrow?

17:44.899 --> 17:45.732
Yeah.

17:46.879 --> 17:49.372
No, I meant, I meant you drive it.

17:49.689 --> 17:50.522
Oh.

17:50.619 --> 17:52.142
Yeah, okay.

17:52.679 --> 17:53.677
I mean, that's the deal, right?

17:53.679 --> 17:54.587
Isn't that we agreed to?

17:54.589 --> 17:55.422
Yeah, mm-hmm.

17:55.609 --> 17:56.442
Cool.

18:00.099 --> 18:01.612
Is she always that chatty?

18:02.569 --> 18:03.402
Yeah.

18:04.069 --> 18:05.219
And full of opinions?

18:05.909 --> 18:06.742
Yup.

18:09.499 --> 18:10.332
Hey.

18:11.077 --> 18:12.352
What the fuck?

18:12.606 --> 18:14.852
The door was open,
didn't you get my text?

18:15.639 --> 18:17.052
No, I was helping Vince.

18:17.549 --> 18:18.382
Who?

18:19.119 --> 18:21.182
Vince, the guy next door.

18:22.129 --> 18:22.962
Oh.

18:26.694 --> 18:27.844
Anyway, this is shit.

18:41.821 --> 18:43.035
Close the door.

19:00.648 --> 19:02.823
Where did that come from?

19:43.428 --> 19:44.261
Ohhh.

19:57.916 --> 19:59.342
It's not raining.

20:00.839 --> 20:02.392
Oops, is that better?

20:02.642 --> 20:04.492
I think that's how they go.

20:05.376 --> 20:10.376
It's all right.

20:10.999 --> 20:12.107
Just focus on the driving.

20:12.109 --> 20:13.709
I'll cover the music, all right?

20:13.879 --> 20:14.712
Okay.

20:16.369 --> 20:17.596
That's better, right?

20:29.419 --> 20:31.022
Let's go to the one in Glendale?

20:31.029 --> 20:31.957
There's one in Riverside.

20:31.959 --> 20:34.357
Yeah, but that'll give
us more time to practice.

20:34.359 --> 20:35.622
Oh, okay.

20:36.683 --> 20:37.514
Is that cool?

20:37.516 --> 20:38.349
Yeah.

20:40.091 --> 20:43.886
You can go faster than three
miles an hour if you want.

21:04.821 --> 21:06.238
Can I have one?

21:22.039 --> 21:24.322
Do not tell your mom, all right?

21:24.739 --> 21:26.677
So you know you shouldn't
give me a cigarette,

21:26.679 --> 21:27.932
but you did anyway.

21:29.889 --> 21:30.957
So now you're gonna give me shit?

21:30.959 --> 21:33.159
You want me to take it back?

21:33.161 --> 21:35.561
I don't know, all that
talk about your thesis.

21:35.829 --> 21:38.232
The right thing to do, what we oughta do.

21:38.516 --> 21:42.349
Now you know why it's
taking me eight years.

23:28.241 --> 23:30.174
Oh, shit.

23:30.176 --> 23:31.312
You scared me.

23:31.352 --> 23:33.557
Your mom said to come get
you, didn't mean to interrupt.

23:33.559 --> 23:34.392
Sorry.

23:36.929 --> 23:38.652
Hey, that's me.

23:39.919 --> 23:40.769
Do you like it?

23:42.119 --> 23:44.132
I mean, I expected you to be good,

23:45.459 --> 23:46.652
but not this good.

23:47.999 --> 23:49.652
I like how thick the paint is.

23:51.324 --> 23:52.724
You almost want to touch it.

23:54.389 --> 23:55.222
Go ahead.

23:56.009 --> 23:58.009
Nah, I wouldn't wanna ruin it.

23:58.659 --> 24:00.482
I can fix it if you do.

24:06.489 --> 24:07.320
Cool.

24:07.322 --> 24:09.202
